        <div n="506-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-1"> The greatest monarch may be stabbed by night,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-2"> And fortune help the murderer in his flight;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-3"> The vilest ruffian may commit a rape,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-4"> Yet safe from injured innocence escape:</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-5"> And calumny, by working underground,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-6"> Can, unrevenged, the greatest merit wound.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="7" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-7">What's to be done? shall wit and learning choose,&#13;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-8"> To live obscure, and have no fame to lose?</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-9"> By censure frighted out of honour's road,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-10"> Nor dare to use the gifts by heaven bestowed;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-11"> Or fearless enter in through virtue's gate,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-506-ROGP-line-12"> And buy distinction at the dearest rate?506-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
